OL,6,F"What we can be is proud of the
OL,7,Fknowledge that our debate is setting a
OL,8,Fglobal example for how to
OL,9,Fdemocratically consider this issue. We
OL,10,Fneed to be actively bringing in the
OL,11,Fconcerns of the elderly and the
OL,12,Fdisabled so that any primary
OL,13,Flegislation gives us the safeguards we
OL,14,Fall expect."
OL,16,FDeputy Phillip Bailhache states: "A
OL,17,Fsociety which tells disabled people
OL,18,Fthat their lives may not be as
OL,19,Fvaluable as those of abled bodies, is
OL,20,Fnot in my view, a compassionate
OL,21,Fsociety."
