OL,3,CJersey politicians begin to announce
OL,4,Cvotes in assisted dying debate
OL,6,FDeputy Helen Miles explains: "Being
OL,7,Fable to die with dignity in a manner
OL,8,Fof one's choosing should be understood
OL,9,Fas a fundamental human right and this
OL,10,Fposition is supported by the European
OL,11,FCourt of Human Rights.
OL,13,F"Palliative care has limits it can
OL,14,Fgive everyone the good death that they
OL,15,Fmight wish for, it is unjust to force
OL,16,Findividuals to endure unbearable pain
OL,17,Fwhen the means exist to end their
OL,18,Fsuffering peacefully."
